Mercury Systems, Inc.( NASDAQ: MRCY ) is a leading commercial provider of secure and safety-critical processing subsystems for defense applications. Headquartered in Andover, Massachusetts, Mercury is pioneering a next-generation defense electronics business model specifically designed to meet the industry’s current and emerging technology needs.[4] Mercury has supplied processing subsystems to over 30 prime contractors, in over 300 programs. Their processing subsystems are used in Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR), Radar, Electronic Warfare (EW), storage and guidance defense applications.[5]



Contents


1 History
2 Products and Services

2.1 Mercury's Next Generation Business Model
2.2 Open System Architecture (OSA) for Digital and RF/Microwave Processing
