Mercury Systems, Inc. Key Developments

Mercury Systems Inc. Receives $6.3 Million Order for Surveillance Radar Processing
Jul 20 17
Mercury Systems Inc. announced that it received a $6.3 million order from a leading defense prime contractor for radar processing products. The order includes solutions for multiple surveillance programs and platforms ranging from high-altitude reconnaissance to maritime surveillance in both manned and unmanned aircraft. The order is expected to be shipped over the next several quarters.


Mercury Systems Inc Wins $10.5 Million Follow-on Order
Jul 17 17
Mercury Systems Inc. announced that it won a $10.5 million follow-on order from a defense prime contractor for high-performance microwave transceivers for precision guided munitions. The order was booked in the company's fiscal fourth quarter and is expected to be shipped over the next several quarters.


Mercury Systems Gets $8 Million Order for Precision Guided Munitions Applications
Jun 28 17
Mercury Systems announced that it has received an $8 million follow-on order from an unidentified defense prime contractor. Mercury will provide GPS selective availability anti-spoofing modules (SAASM) for a precision guided munitions program. The order was booked in the company's fourth quarter and is expected to be shipped over the next several quarters.


